<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="296" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2353½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">17 January, 1916</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: This draft has my
                            entire approval. I hope that you will send it to the Governments you
                            have indicated to me; and I most sincerely hope that they will feel that
                            we are right in our argument and suggestion and will be willing to
                            cooperate with us in attaining the object we have in view, an object
                            which they must surely wish to accomplish as earnestly as we do, and
                            which this seems in the circumstances the only feasible way of
                            reaching.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>